Manage Decision Optimization (Beta)
You are here: Manage Decision Optimization (Beta)

You can manage Decision Optimizations from the Model Manager, along with your deployed and uploaded models.

View Optimizations

COLUMN	DESCRIPTION
Optimization	The name of the decision optimization.
Goal	The objective of the optimization to improve (maximize or minimize).
Object	The Salesforce object the optimization is deployed to.
Model	The subject of optimization. Must be a deployed Einstein Discovery model.
Last Updated	Date and time when the optimization was last updated.
Status	Indicates the current standing of the optimization, such as succeeded, failed, or running.

Manage Optimizations

Use the dropdown to take action on optimizations.

Explore the dataset of optimization results.
Edit the optimization to make changes.
Run Now to manually initiate the optimization to run without making any changes.
Cancel Run to stop the optimization run before it completes.
Delete the optimization.
title: Managing Decision Optimization in Salesforce
